text: Cheslie Corrinne Kryst (April 28, 1991 â€“ January 30, 2022) was an American beauty queen and television presenter. She won Miss USA in 2019. She also represented the United States in Miss Universe. Kryst was born in Jackson, Michigan. From 2019 until her death, she was a presenter for the television show Extra. Kryst, aged 30, jumped off from her New York City apartment building on January 30, 2022. ==References== Category:1991 births Category:2022 deaths Category:American television presenters Category:Miss USA Category:Models from Michigan Category:Entertainers from Michigan Category:Suicides by jumping in the United States Category:Suicide in 2022
